SIMPLE: peeper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peeper
<hw>Peep"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A chicken
just breaking the shell; a young bird.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who peeps; a prying person; a spy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who's there? <qex>peepers</qex>, . . . eavesdroppers?</q>
<rj><qau>J. Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The eye; <as>as, to close the
<ex>peepers</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peephole</ent>⟦br⟧
